Carl Sagan (1934-1996) was an American astronomer, cosmologist, and author.
Short quotations from his published works are used here under fair use for
educational, transformative, and non-commercial purposes. Many of these
passages have entered common usage and are widely quoted in public discourse.

Sources include: Cosmos (1980), Pale Blue Dot (1994), The Demon-Haunted World
(1995), Contact (1985), Billions & Billions (1997), The Dragons of Eden (1977),
Broca's Brain (1979), The Cosmic Connection (1973), Shadows of Forgotten
Ancestors (1992), A Path Where No Man Thought (1990), The Varieties of
Scientific Experience (2006), and various speeches, essays, and interviews.
